a) Herman Vanden Hoogen Bros., R.R. #2, Mabou;
(b)	The highest purchase price was $180,500;
(c)	Yes, it was the highest bid received; and
(d)	All of the potential purchasers planned to use the Mabou farm for agriculture purposes although their individual business plans differed. The successful bidder focused his plans on livestock and dairy operations.
